definition.value: An alpha-amino-acid cation that is the conjugate acid of sarcosine, arising from protonation of the amino group.

A dialdehyde that is cyclopentanecarbaldehyde substituted by a methyl group at position 2 and a 3-oxo-prop-1-en-2yl group at position 5. It has been found to occur in pheromones of insects such as aphids.
A hydroxypolyether that is nonaethylene glycol in which one of the terminal hydroxy functions is substituted by a lauryl (dodecyl) group.
A pyridinedicarboxylic acid carrying carboxy groups at positions 2 and 5.
A carboxypyridinecarboxylate that is the conjugate base of isocinchomeronic acid.
A pyridinedicarboxylate that is the  conjugate base of isocinchomeronate(1-).
The amino acid ester derivative obtained the formal condensation of an alpha-amino acid with an alcohol.
An amino group formed by replacement of one of the hydrogen atoms in ammonia by a group or atom other than a hydrogen atom.
An organic radical derived from  acetaldehyde.
A triacyl lipopeptide that is the pentapeptide Cys-Ser-Lys-Lys-Lys-Lys in which the side-chain thiol hydrogen on the Cys residue has been replaced by a 2,3-bis(palmitoyloxy)propyl group.
